            <div class="terms-conditions" style="font-size: 10px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 16px;">
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>1. MEMBERSHIP</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">1.1 The group shall consist of not less than ten (10) members at the time of formation.</div>
                    <div>1.2 All members shall provide full names, national ID numbers, and signatures.</div>
                    <div>1.3 Membership shall be voluntary and open to individuals who share the group's objectives.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>2. PURPOSE AND OBJECTIVES</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">2.1 The group shall be formed for lawful and non-political purposes.</div>
                    <div>2.2 The group shall have a clearly defined objective, including but not limited to: Economic empowerment, Social development, Savings and investment (chama activities).</div>
                    <div>2.3 All activities of the group shall align with its stated objectives.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>3. LEGAL COMPLIANCE</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">3.1 The group shall comply with all applicable regulations under the Ministry of Labour and Social Protection.</div>
                    <div>3.2 The group shall not engage in illegal, harmful, or unethical activities.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>4. LEADERSHIP STRUCTURE</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">4.1 The group shall elect the following officials: Chairperson, Secretary, Treasurer.</div>
                    <div>4.2 Elections shall be conducted democratically during the formation meeting.</div>
                    <div>4.3 Officials shall serve with integrity and accountability.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>5. CONSTITUTION</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">5.1 The group shall adopt a written constitution during its formation.</div>
                    <div>5.2 The constitution shall define: Membership rules, Leadership roles, Meeting procedures, Financial management.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>6. GROUP NAME</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">6.1 The group shall adopt a unique and acceptable name.</div>
                    <div>6.2 The name shall not: Duplicate an existing group in the same area, Be offensive or misleading.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>7. FORMATION MEETING RESOLUTION</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">7.1 A formal meeting shall be held to: Approve the formation of the group, Adopt the group name, Elect officials.</div>
                    <div>7.2 The resolutions shall be recorded in official meeting proceedings (minutes).</div>
                    <div>7.3 The proceedings shall be signed by the Chairperson, Secretary, and members present.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>8. QUORUM</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">8.1 The formation meeting shall only be valid if a minimum required number of members (quorum) is present.</div>
                    <div>8.2 No decisions shall be made without quorum.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>9. AREA OF OPERATION</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">9.1 The group shall operate within a defined geographical area (village, ward, or sub-county).</div>
                    <div>9.2 Members shall preferably reside within the same locality.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>10. FINANCIAL PROVISIONS</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">10.1 Members shall agree on regular contributions.</div>
                    <div>10.2 The group shall maintain proper financial records.</div>
                    <div>10.3 A group bank account shall be opened upon registration where applicable.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>11. ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">11.1 Members must be adults with valid identification.</div>
                    <div>11.2 Youth groups shall consist of members within the recognized youth age bracket.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="term-item">
                    <strong>12. ADOPTION OF TERMS</strong>
                    <div style="margin-top:4px;">12.1 These terms and conditions shall be read, understood, and adopted by all members during the formation meeting.</div>
                    <div>12.2 Adoption shall be confirmed through signatures of members present.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.4; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 20px; padding: 12px; background: var(--accent-light); border-radius: 6px;">
                <strong>✅ DECLARATION</strong><br>
                We, the undersigned members, agree to abide by the above terms and conditions for the formation and restructure important instructions with above content.
            </div>
        </section>

